      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Agents -> System Instructions -> Prompts\n\nPrompts -> Multi steps instructions -> 1. Read the mail understand the context\n2. Classify what kind of issue 3. Draft an email based on the context and issue and \ngive reply\n\n\nThe core problem is ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Agents -> System Instructions -> Prompts\n\nPrompts -> Multi steps instructions -> 1. Read the mail understand the context\n2. Classify what kind of issue 3. Draft an email based on the context and issue and \ngive reply\n\n\nThe core problem is ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "97nu3z_6l0RY6FIIBcS7w",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 262,
      "y": 469,
      "width": 637.859619140625,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 506776147,
      "version": 315,
      "versionNonce": 2036907443,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779630656806,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. The instructions are treated as suggestions not rules\n2. In long prompts, few steps can be missed\n3. In sometime steps can be clubbed together\n4. Long prompts make the output very unpredictable\n5. You can track or trace how each steps in prompts are covered.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. The instructions are treated as suggestions not rules\n2. In long prompts, few steps can be missed\n3. In sometime steps can be clubbed together\n4. Long prompts make the output very unpredictable\n5. You can track or trace how each steps in prompts are covered.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PcAGlw8PGalZkq6Swwnp2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 198,
      "y": 668,
      "width": 1314.559326171875,
      "height": 2100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1255641117,
      "version": 1979,
      "versionNonce": 283737907,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779637511474,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Graph flows:\n\nWe clearly define the steps one by one:\n\nSTART -> Read the mail  ->  Classify -> Draft Email -> END\n\n\nAdvantages:\n\n1. predictable execution\n2. Reliability\n3. Easier Debugging\n4. Safer Enterprise workflow\n\n\nHere Each node represent task:\n\nThe task can be two things:\n\n1. AI Node -> Reasoning purposes\n2. Python function Node -> Python logic\n\n\nAI + python node -> Graph workflows\n\n-> AI powered\n-> Deterministic flows\n\n\n\n\nDifference with Graph workflow vs workflow agents\n\n\n1. Orchestration -> \n\nOther worflow Agents :We defined the order/ LLM decides what order to execute\nGraph workflow :  The code decides what order it should execute.\n\n2. branching:\n\nOther worflow Agents : We defined the branches / LLM decides it \nGraph workflow :  Entire branching will be done by the routers\n\n3. Realibility:\n\nOther worflow Agents : High\nGraph workflow :  Very High Reliable\n\n\n4. AI + Code:\nOther worflow Agents : Fully AI\nGraph workflow :  Node can be both or either\n\n\nGraph Anatonomy:\n\nThere 4 major bulding block\n\n1. Agent Node -> LLM node -> uses LLM/ input_schema/output_schema to pass it into the node\n2. Function Node -> Plain python function -> No LLM involved. Deterministic Node. Basically used for routing and transformation logics\n3. Workflow Node -> A nested sub-workflow used as single node inside parent node. \n4. Join Node-> it waits for the all the parallel above node to finish and take the combined output to next node.\n\n\n\n Events flows between nodes:\n\n1. Output -> pass data to next data -> Event(Output = )\n2. route -> trigger a branch -> Event(route -= 'Quality')\n3. message -> Final user facing response -> Event(message = \"Audit complete\")\n4. output + route -> Pass data and branch -> Event(Output = , route = )\n\n\n\n    \n\nproducts\nparts\nassembles\nsuppliers\ncomplaints\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Graph flows:\n\nWe clearly define the steps one by one:\n\nSTART -> Read the mail  ->  Classify -> Draft Email -> END\n\n\nAdvantages:\n\n1. predictable execution\n2. Reliability\n3. Easier Debugging\n4. Safer Enterprise workflow\n\n\nHere Each node represent task:\n\nThe task can be two things:\n\n1. AI Node -> Reasoning purposes\n2. Python function Node -> Python logic\n\n\nAI + python node -> Graph workflows\n\n-> AI powered\n-> Deterministic flows\n\n\n\n\nDifference with Graph workflow vs workflow agents\n\n\n1. Orchestration -> \n\nOther worflow Agents :We defined the order/ LLM decides what order to execute\nGraph workflow :  The code decides what order it should execute.\n\n2. branching:\n\nOther worflow Agents : We defined the branches / LLM decides it \nGraph workflow :  Entire branching will be done by the routers\n\n3. Realibility:\n\nOther worflow Agents : High\nGraph workflow :  Very High Reliable\n\n\n4. AI + Code:\nOther worflow Agents : Fully AI\nGraph workflow :  Node can be both or either\n\n\nGraph Anatonomy:\n\nThere 4 major bulding block\n\n1. Agent Node -> LLM node -> uses LLM/ input_schema/output_schema to pass it into the node\n2. Function Node -> Plain python function -> No LLM involved. Deterministic Node. Basically used for routing and transformation logics\n3. Workflow Node -> A nested sub-workflow used as single node inside parent node. \n4. Join Node-> it waits for the all the parallel above node to finish and take the combined output to next node.\n\n\n\n Events flows between nodes:\n\n1. Output -> pass data to next data -> Event(Output = )\n2. route -> trigger a branch -> Event(route -= 'Quality')\n3. message -> Final user facing response -> Event(message = \"Audit complete\")\n4. output + route -> Pass data and branch -> Event(Output = , route = )\n\n\n\n    \n\nproducts\nparts\nassembles\nsuppliers\ncomplaints\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
